- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper uses analytical combinatorial tools to analyze the algorithm's runtime. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is another possible category as the paper deals with the OneMax benchmark function, which is a well-known discrete optimization problem. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper uses asymptotic techniques to analyze the algorithm's runtime. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a possible category as the paper deals with the analysis of the runtime of an algorithm on a specific problem.
